<!-- Fluid Scaling Section -->
<section id="fluid-scaling">
  <h2>Fluid Scaling</h2>
  <p>Add <code>data-fluid</code> to the <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> element to make type sizes and spacing scale continuously across viewports. Instead of breakpoint jumps, values interpolate smoothly from 320px to 1440px using <code>clamp()</code>.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Enable fluid scaling">{{ '<!-- Default preset -->\n<html data-fluid>\n\n<!-- Presets -->\n<html data-fluid="compact">\n<html data-fluid="spacious">\n\n<!-- Combine with themes -->\n<html data-theme="ocean" data-fluid>' | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>Presets</h3>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Preset</th><th>Type Ratio</th><th>Space Swing</th><th>Character</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>compact</code></td><td>1.067 &rarr; 1.2</td><td>&plusmn;11%</td><td>Tight, uniform hierarchy</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>default</code></td><td>1.125 &rarr; 1.25</td><td>&plusmn;10%</td><td>Balanced, general-purpose</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>spacious</code></td><td>1.2 &rarr; 1.333</td><td>&plusmn;11%</td><td>Generous, dramatic headings</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>Fluid scaling composes with all themes. The <code>a11y-large-text</code> accessibility theme includes its own fluid compound rules so the larger base sizes also scale fluidly.</p>
  <p>For custom fluid parameters, see the <a href="/docs/tools/fluid-layout/">Fluid Sizing tool</a> and <a href="/lab/experiments/theme-composer/">Theme Composer</a>.</p>
</section>

